<h3>Latest Earnings · Q1 FY2026 · Mar 4, 2026</h3>
<p>Broadcom delivered a massive beat: <span class="hl">$19.3B</span> revenue (+29% YoY) vs $19.26B est, non-GAAP EPS <span class="hl">$2.05</span> vs $2.02 est. AI semiconductor revenue hit <span class="hl">$8.4B (+106% YoY)</span> — above forecast. Adj EBITDA record $13.1B (68%). FCF $8.0B (41% margin). Q2 guide: <span class="hl">$22.0B (+47% YoY)</span> with AI semi revenue of $10.7B (+140% YoY). Customer base expanded to 6 hyperscalers. CEO Hock Tan stated "line of sight" to <span class="hl">>$100B AI chip revenue in FY2027</span>. $10B new buyback + $0.65/q dividend. Google and Anthropic long-term supply agreements announced in April. TSMC capacity flagged as bottleneck — fully stretched through 2028.</p>
